%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20one%2C%20I%20did%20not%20add%20a%20line%20about%20brevity%2C%20resulting%20in%20all%20of%20the%20models%20churning%20out%20responses%20that%20were%20far%20too%20long.%20Interestingly%2C%20GPT-4o%20wrote%20the%20longest%20email%2C%20at%20nearly%20300%20words.%20The%20other%20two%20were%20around%20250.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20emails%20were%20structured%20very%20similarly.%20For%20example%2C%20all%20three%20lost%20sight%20of%20the%20topic%20and%20thanked%20the%20email%20recipient%20for%20%26quot%3Bconsidering%20my%20application.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20GPT-4o%20model%20and%20the%203.5%20model%20added%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3BWhat%20sets%20me%20apart%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%20which%20indicated%20to%20me%20that%20it%20was%20pulling%20from%20my%20prompt.%20It%20was%20something%20I%20would%20expect%20to%20read%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20a%20middle%20school%20essay%20%E2%80%94%20not%20from%20an%20adult%20job%20seeker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWinner%3A%20GPT-4%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAnd%20the%20winner%20is...%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221216%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ChatGPT%20logo%20repeated%20three%20times%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664930209fc063e829b2a716%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22912%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT%20will%20be%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bot%20has%20a%20distinct%20voice%20and%20style%20that%20makes%20it%20obvious%20that%20a%20non-human%20is%20composing%20whatever%20text%20output%20you%20ask%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20the%20newer%20model%20has%20shed%20that%20sound%20on%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20though%20maybe%20having%20the%20text%20read%20aloud%20by%20a%20human-sounding%2C%20and%20perhaps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt4o-chatgpt-voice-flirty-her-ick-sam-altman-2024-5%5C%22%20