2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20James%20collapses%20and%20is%20hurried%20back%20to%20his%20countryside%20estate%2C%20they%20concoct%20a%20plan%20to%20make%20sure%20these%20orders%20aren't%20acted%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f99562e3-3ac8-4dd6-b667-6d0cfce31903%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20ending%20used%20is%20'true%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20how%20Mary%20and%20George%20lived%20their%20lives'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%2C%20who%20co-wrote%20the%20finale%20with%20Laura%20Grace%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20for%20him%2C%20the%20ending%20was%20%26quot%3Btrue%20to%20the%20spirit%26quot%3B%20of%20Mary%20and%20George's%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20diverges%20from%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20royal's%20official%20cause%20of%20death%20at%20age%2058%20in%201625%20was%20listed%20as%20a%20stroke%20and%20an%20attack%20of%20dysentery%2C%20complicated%20by%20a%20disease%20such%20as%20malaria%20or%20typhus%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.historyextra.com%2Fperiod%2Fstuart%2Fhow-did-james-vi-i-die-was-murdered%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%20History%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Moore%2C%20different%20endings%20were%20floated%20but%20ultimately%20scrapped%20in%20favor%20of%20an%20ending%20that%20embodied%20the%20push-and-pull%20relationships%20of%20the%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nicholas%20Galitzine%20as%20George%20Villiers%20in%20the%20finale%20of%C2%A0%26quot%3BMary%20%26amp%3B%20George.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6648a4db9fc063e829b2a3a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENicholas%20Galitzine%20as%20George%20Villiers%20in%C2%A0%26quot%3BMary%20%26amp%3B%20George.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ERory%20Mulvey%2FStarz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20experiment%20with%20different%20ideas%2C%20but%20it%20felt%20more%20and%20more%20inevitable%20to%20end%20it%20this%20way.%20Because%20I%20think%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20real%20history%2C%20what%20is%20true%20then%20you%20see%20that%20James%20was%20a%20king%20of%20peace%2C%20and%20George%20bought%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20killing%20of%20James%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20he's%20killing%20peace%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20and%20his%20cowriter%20didn't%20come%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20entirely%20themselves%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20took%20some%20inspiration%20from%20Benjamin%20Woolley's%20historical%20biography%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20King's%20Assassin%3A%20The%20Secret%20Plot%20to%20Murder%20James%20I%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20which%20the%20series%20is%20based.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoolley%20posited%20in%20the%20book%20that%20Mary%20and%20George%20were%20by%20the%20king's%20bedside%20as%20he%20recovered%20from%20a%20bout%20of%20malaria-like%20fever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20in%20the%20room%20was%20James's%20son%20and%20heir%2C%20Charles%2C%20whom%20Woolley%20theorized%20had%20colluded%20with%20George%20to%20kill%20his%20father%20to%20ensure%20his%20ascendancy%20to%20the%20throne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20was%20in%20that%20room%20other%20than%20those%20three%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20some%20level%20of%20dramatic%20license%20that%20we've%20taken%2C%20but%20for%20me%2C%20it%20feels%20very%20true%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20how%20Mary%20and%20George%20lived%20their%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20series%20depicts%2C%20once%20Charles%20became%20king%2C%20George%20retained%20his%20powerful%20position%20in%20court%20until%20he%20himself%20was%20assassinated%20in%201628%2C%20at%20age%2035.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20dancing%20around%20the%20history.%20There%20is%20some%20creation%20on%20our%20side%20but%20I%20think%20also%20we're%20not%20that%20far%20from%20the%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20added.%3C%2Fp%