0%20chance%20of%20getting%20laboratory-confirmed%20norovirus%20during%20an%20outbreak%20on%20ship%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcruising.org%2Fen-gb%2Fabout-the-industry%2Fpolicy-priorities%2Fhealth%2Fnorovirus-on-cruise-ships%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECruise%20Lines%20International%20Association%20says%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20P%26amp%3BO%20website%2C%20Ventura%20has%20capacity%20for%203%2C078%20guests%20and%201%2C205%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorovirus%20is%20one%20possible%20cause%20of%20the%20guests'%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bvomiting%20bug%2C%26quot%3B%20norovirus%20is%20a%20highly%20contagious%20stomach%20bug%20that%20causes%20vomiting%20and%20diarrhea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20spread%20via%20close%20contact%20with%20someone%20who%20has%20the%20bug%2C%20touching%20your%20mouth%20after%20touching%20contaminated%20surfaces%20or%20objects%2C%20or%20eating%20contaminated%20food%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UK's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhs.uk%2Fconditions%2Fnorovirus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Health%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20confined%20areas%20such%20as%20a%20cruise%20ship%2C%20the%20virus%20can%20spread%20particularly%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20experienced%20a%20period%20of%20high%20norovirus%20activity%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20weeks%2014%20to%2017%20of%202024%2C%20the%20total%20number%20of%20norovirus%20laboratory%20reports%20was%2075%25%20higher%20than%20the%205-season%20average%20for%20the%20same%204-week%20period%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20UK%20government%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20over%20120%20passengers%20on%20board%20Cunard's%20Queen%20Victoria%20ship%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcunard-cruise-ship-passengers-fell-ill-from-unknown-cause-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20having%20diarrhea%20and%20vomiting.%20It%20was%20later%20revealed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fvessel-sanitation%2Fcruise-ship-outbreaks%2Fqueen-victoria-january-2024.html%3FCDC_AAref_Val%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Fvsp%2Fsurv%2Foutbreak%2F2024%2FQueen-Victoria-1-29.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enorovirus%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20caused%20the%20sickness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20CDC%20reported%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrity-cruises-constellation-cruise-ship-norovirus-stomach-flu-outbreak-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoutbreak%20of%20norovirus%20on%20a%20Celebrity%20Cruises%20ship%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20agency%20said%20100%20people%2C%20including%20passengers%20and%20crew%2C%20reported%20symptoms%20of%20vomiting%20and%20diarrhea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CDC%20had%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fvessel-sanitation%2Fcruise-ship-outbreaks%2F%3FCDC_AAref_Val%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Fvsp%2Fsurv%2Fgilist.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elogged%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20total%20of%20six%20outbreaks%20of%20gastrointestinal%20diseases%20aboard%20cruise%20ships%20so%20far%20this%20year.%20Five%20of%20those%20were%20due%20to%20norovirus%2C%20while%20one%20was%20said%20to%20have%20been%20caused%20by%20E.%20Coli.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-250-passengers-fall-ill-with-suspected-norovirus-cruise-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716036390000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65602b5222cf74a5739c0878%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-250-passengers-fall-ill-with-suspected-norovirus-cruise-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20P%26amp%3BO%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20there%20had%20been%20numero