ions%2C%20which%20escalated%20in%202016-17.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20time%20when%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20money%20to%20pay%20my%20son%E2%80%99s%20school%20fees%2C%20and%20had%20to%20borrow%20money%20for%20the%20same%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Sreejith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20they%20ever%20consider%20quitting%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%E2%80%9D%20comes%20the%20answer%20in%20unison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20you%20quit%20a%20corporate%20career%2C%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20go%20back.%20We%20just%20had%20a%20sliver%20of%20hope%20that%20we%20stretched%2C%20leading%20us%20here%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20smiles%20Sreejith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20money%20and%20bills%20piling%20up%20at%20home%2C%20the%20duo%20picked%20up%20consulting%20jobs%20to%20ensure%20some%20cash%20flow%20at%20home.%20Another%20facet%20adding%20to%20their%20woes%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20were%20related%2C%20with%20many%20advising%20them%20not%20to%20do%20business%20together%2C%20as%20it%20may%20sour%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20kept%20at%20it%2C%20as%20they%20were%20sure%20of%20their%20vision%20%E2%80%94%20making%20people%20realise%20the%20importance%20of%20health%20before%20it%20gets%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20challenges%20continued%20even%20as%20True%20Elements%20picked%20up%2C%20as%20an%20investor%20hung%20them%20dry%20just%20before%20the%20lockdown%20in%20March%202020.%20By%20this%20time%20they%20had%20over%20100%20employees%20and%20salaries%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20principle%2C%20we%20are%20true%20to%20our%20employees%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20cut%20salaries.%20But%20COVID-19%20was%20a%20tough%20time%20as%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20money.%20We%20asked%20our%20employees%20personally%20as%20to%20who%20would%20be%20okay%20with%20a%20deferment%20of%20salary%2C%20and%20we%20were%20just%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20response.%20Their%20wholehearted%20willingness%20and%20trust%20in%20us%20pulled%20us%20t